meanings.definition: To make worse; to make inferior in quality or value; to impair.
To grow worse; to be impaired in quality; to degenerate.

examples: to deteriorate the mind

chinese_meanings.definition: 使情况变得更糟；降低质量或价值；损害。
变得更糟；质量受损；退化。

meanings.definition: A place for storing large amounts of products. In logistics, a place where products go to from the manufacturer before going to the retailer.
To store in a warehouse or similar.
To confine (a person) to an institution for a long period.
To acquire and then shelve, simply to prevent competitors from acquiring it.

examples: the warehousing of syndicated TV shows

chinese_meanings.definition: 存放大量产品的地方。在物流中，产品从制造商运往零售商之前的地方。
存放在仓库或类似场所。
将（人）长期限制在某个机构内。

meanings.definition: A deciduous tree with distinctive deeply lobed leaves, acorns, and notably strong wood, typically of England and northeastern North America, included in genus Quercus.
The wood of the oak.
A rich brown colour, like that of oak wood.
Any tree of the genus Quercus, in family Fagaceae.
Any tree of other genera and species of trees resembling typical oaks of genus Quercus in some ways.
The outer (lockable) door of a set of rooms in a college or similar institution. (Often in the phrase "to sport one's oak").
The flavor of oak.
To expose to oak in order for the oak to impart its flavors.
Having a rich brown colour, like that of oak wood.
Made of oak wood or timber

examples: an oak table, oak beam, etc

chinese_meanings.definition: 一种落叶树，具有独特的深裂叶、橡子和特别坚固的木材，通常产于英格兰和北美洲东北部，属于栎属。
橡木的木材。
浓郁的棕色，像橡木的颜色。

meanings.definition: The visible part of fire; a stream of burning vapour or gas, emitting light and heat.
A romantic partner or lover in a usually short-lived but passionate affair.
Intentionally insulting criticism or remark meant to incite anger.
A brilliant reddish orange-gold fiery colour.
The contrasting light and dark figure seen in wood used for stringed instrument making; the curl.
Burning zeal, passion, imagination, excitement, or anger.
To produce flames; to burn with a flame or blaze.
To burst forth like flame; to break out in violence of passion; to be kindled with zeal or ardour.
To post a destructively critical or abusive message (to somebody).
Of a brilliant reddish orange-gold colour, like that of a flame.

examples: The cello has a two-piece back with a beautiful narrow flame.
I flamed him for spamming in my favourite newsgroup.

chinese_meanings.definition: 火的可见部分；燃烧的蒸气或气体流，发出光和热。
一段通常短暂但充满激情的恋情中的浪漫伴侣或情人。
故意侮辱性批评或旨在煽动愤怒的言论。

meanings.definition: To act as president or chairperson.
To exercise authority or control, oversit.
To be a featured solo performer.

chinese_meanings.definition: 担任主席或主席。
为了行使权力或控制权，请过度监督。
成为一名有特色的独奏演员。

meanings.definition: An incidental remark made quietly so as to be heard by the person to whom it is said and not by any others in the vicinity.
A brief comment by a character addressing the audience, unheard by other characters.
A minor related mention, an afterthought.
To or on one side so as to be out of the way.

examples: Move aside, please, so that these people can come through.

chinese_meanings.definition: 轻声说的偶然言论，以便被说这句话的人听到，而不是被附近的任何其他人听到。
一个角色向观众发表的简短评论，其他角色听不到。
一个小的相关提及，事后的想法。

meanings.definition: Wanton or unrestrained behavior; uproar; tumult.
The tumultuous disturbance of the public peace by an unlawful assembly of three or more persons in the execution of some private object.
A wide and unconstrained variety.
Excessive and expensive feasting; wild and loose festivity; revelry.
To create or take part in a riot; to raise an uproar or sedition.
To act in an unrestrained or wanton manner; to indulge in excess of feasting, luxury, etc.
To cause to riot; to throw into a tumult.
To annoy.

examples: In summer this flower garden is a riot of colour.
The nuclear protesters rioted outside the military base.

chinese_meanings.definition: 肆意或无节制的行为；骚动；骚乱。
三人或三人以上非法集会以执行某些私人目的，扰乱公共秩序。
品种广泛且不受限制。

meanings.definition: A violent flow, as of water, lava, etc.; a stream suddenly raised and running rapidly, as down a precipice.
A large amount or stream of something.
Rolling or rushing in a rapid stream.

examples: A torrent of green and white water broke over the hull of the sail-boat.
They endured a torrent of inquiries.

chinese_meanings.definition: 猛烈的流动，如水、熔岩等；一条小溪突然上涨，急速流淌，就像冲下悬崖一样。
大量或大量的东西。
在急流中滚动或冲刷。

meanings.definition: One who exerts power, or has the power to act
One who acts for, or in the place of, another (the principal), by authority from him/her; someone entrusted to do the business of another
A person who looks for work for another person
Someone who works for an intelligence agency
An active power or cause or substance; something which has the power to produce an effect

In the client-server model, the part of the system that performs information preparation and exchange on behalf of a client or server. Especially in the phrase “intelligent agent” it implies some kind of autonomous process which can communicate with other agents to perform some collective task on behalf of one or more humans.
(grammar) The participant of a situation that carries out the action in this situation, e.g. "the boy" in the sentences "The boy kicked the ball" and "The ball was kicked by the boy".
A cheat who is assisted by dishonest casino staff.

chinese_meanings.definition: 行使权力或有权力采取行动的人
依据另一人（委托人）的授权，为另一人（委托人）行事或代替另一人（委托人）行事的人；受委托做他人生意的人
为另一个人找工作的人

meanings.definition: A person in a marriage or marital relationship.
To wed; to espouse.

examples: People should treat their spouses with respect.

chinese_meanings.definition: 处于婚姻或婚姻关系中的人。
结婚；去拥护。

meanings.definition: A slender wax candle; a small lighted wax candle
(by extension) a small light.
A tapering form; gradual diminution of thickness and/or cross section in an elongated object
A thin stick used for lighting candles, either a wax-coated wick or a slow-burning wooden rod.
To make thinner or narrower at one end.
To diminish gradually.
Tapered; narrowing to a point.

examples: The legs of the table had a slight taper to them.

chinese_meanings.definition: 一根细长的蜡烛；一支点燃的小蜡烛
（推而广之）一盏小灯。
锥形形式；细长物体的厚度和/或横截面逐渐减小

meanings.definition: (of a statement) Arousing doubt; questionable; open to suspicion.
(of a person) In disbelief; wavering, uncertain, or hesitating in opinion; inclined to doubt; undecided.

examples: After he made some dubious claims about the company, fewer people trusted him.
She was dubious about my plan at first, but later I managed to persuade her to cooperate.

chinese_meanings.definition: （陈述）引起怀疑；有疑问的；容易受到怀疑。
（某人）难以置信；意见摇摆不定、不确定或犹豫；倾向于怀疑；尚未决定。

meanings.definition: (historical: 19th-century Britain) A member of the most progressive wing of the Liberal Party; someone favouring social reform (but generally stopping short of socialism).
(historical: early 20th-century France) A member of an influential, centrist political party favouring moderate social reform, a republican constitution, and secular politics.
A person with radical opinions.
A root (of a number or quantity).
In logographic writing systems such as the Chinese writing system, the portion of a character (if any) that provides an indication of its meaning, as opposed to phonetic.
In Semitic languages, any one of the set of consonants (typically three) that make up a root.
A group of atoms, joined by covalent bonds, that take part in reactions as a single unit.
A free radical.

(commutative algebra, of an ideal) Given an ideal I in a commutative ring R, another ideal, denoted Rad(I) or \sqrt{I}, such that an element x ∈ R is in Rad(I) if, for some positive integer n, xn ∈ I; equivalently, the intersection of all prime ideals containing I.
(of a ring) Given a ring R, an ideal containing elements of R that share a property considered, in some sense, "not good".
(of a module) The intersection of maximal submodules of a given module.
The product of the distinct prime factors of a given positive integer.
Favoring fundamental change, or change at the root cause of a matter.
Pertaining to a root (of a plant).
Pertaining to the basic or intrinsic nature of something.
Thoroughgoing; far-reaching.
Of or pertaining to the root of a word.
(of a sound) Produced using the root of the tongue.
Involving free radicals.
Relating to a radix or mathematical root.
(1980s & 1990s) Excellent; awesome.

examples: His beliefs are radical.
The spread of the cancer required radical surgery, and the entire organ was removed.
a radical quantity; a radical sign
That was a radical jump!

chinese_meanings.definition: （历史：19世纪的英国）自由党最进步派的成员；支持社会改革（但通常不支持社会主义）的人。
（历史：20世纪初的法国）一个有影响力的中间派政党的成员，主张温和的社会改革、共和宪法和世俗政治。
具有激进观点的人。

meanings.definition: To attribute a cause or characteristic to someone or something.
To attribute a book, painting or any work of art or literature to a writer or creator.
(with to) To believe in or agree with; subscribe.

examples: One may ascribe these problems to the federal government; however, at this stage it is unclear what caused them.
It is arguable as to whether we can truly ascribe this play to Shakespeare.

chinese_meanings.definition: 将原因或特征归因于某人或某事。
将书籍、绘画或任何艺术或文学作品归因于作家或创作者。
（with to）相信或同意；订阅。
